Solve : 2x^4 > 3x^3 + 9x^2

move all terms to one side
2x^4 - 3x^3 - 9x^2 > 0

factor out common terms

x^2(2x^2 - 3x - 9) > 0

solve the equation:

1. x^2 = 0 -> x = 0

2. 2x^2 - 3x - 9 = 0

